# TypeScript

- Prefer explicit types at module boundaries (public exports, API clients, DTOs).
- Don’t “any” your way out; fix the type at the source if possible.
- Keep exports clean: packages should export from a single public entry (e.g., src/index.ts).
- Avoid cross-importing deep internals of other packages unless explicitly intended.
